text: Susan Ann Sulley (sometimes known as Susan Ann Gayle; born 22 March 1963) is a British singer-songwriter. She began singing at age 17. She worked with The Human League and had major hit singles with them, including "Human" in 1986. Sulley was born in Sheffield, West Riding of Yorkshire, England. ==References== Category:1963 births Category:Living people Category:English pop musicians Category:English singers Category:Musicians from Sheffield Category:New wave singers
